frameDefinitions: A Cognizer thinks of and performs an Action that is a self- or other-imposed task or some other kind of desirable behavior.
An Agent causes a Firearm to discharge which induces the rapid motion of the Projectile.
An Agent acts according to a <em>
An Agent acts to begin the life of a Process.
An Agent  places a Component in a Fixed_location so that the Component is attached and interconnected and thereby functional.
Generally without overall (translational) motion,  an Agent places a Theme at a location, the Goal, which is profiled.

listRoleDefinitions: The person who thinks of or fails to think of an obligatory or desireable <fen>Action</fen>.
An <fen>Action</fen> that the <fen>Cognizer</fen> is supposed to carry out. This may be a Task imposed specifically on the <fen>Cognizer</fen> or it may be self- or socially imposed.
The <fen>Salient_entity</fen> is a person or thing that the <fen>Cognizer</fen> needs to affect or effect when carrying out the <fen>Action</fen>.
A <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Cognizer</fen> remembers or fails to carry out an <fen>Action</fen>.
The entity whose rapid, dangerous motion is caused by the Agent and/or Firearm.
The Agent is the person performing the intentional act causing the motion of the Projectile.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the shooting event takes place.
The location in which the shooting event takes place.
The <fen>Plan</fen> is a goal or purpose that the <fen>Agent</fen> carries out.

The <fen>Agent</fen>, often an institution or governmental organization, puts a <fen>Plan</fen> into effect. The Agent is generally a primary participant in the <fen>Plan</fen>, but a separate <fen>Focal_participant</fen> may be specified.
This role describes the medium through which a plan was executed.  It may occur in the same syntactic position as the Agent.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the Agent puts the <fen>Plan</fen> into effect.

The <fen>Place</fen> at which the <fen>Plan</fen> is or is not operational.

[CHANGE: or, place where agent puts into effect? 2 fes?]
This Frame Element marks expressions that indicate the process that the <fen>Agent</fen> initiates.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the actor responsible for starting the <fen>Process</fen>.
This role is for the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> initiates the <fen>Process</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Process</fen> is initiated.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person (or other force) that installs the <fen>Component</fen>.
The <fen>Component</fen> is the object that is placed in a <fen>Fixed_location</fen>.
The <fen>Fixed_location</fen> is the location where the <fen>Component</fen> is placed and to which it is attached so as to be useful.
The time period in which the <fen>Component</fen> is installed.
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates where the installation occurs.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person (or other force) that causes the <fen>Theme</fen> to move.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the object that changes location during the Placing.
The role <fen>Goal</fen> is the location where the <fen>Theme</fen> ends up. This role is profiled by words in this frame.
<fen>Time</fen> is when the Placing occurs
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates where the Placing occurs.
